The paper introduces a new solution concept for non-cooperative games in normal form, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The concept involves players being perfect predictors, which could also be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the computation of the equilibrium, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions Pareto optimality, which is a concept in multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
